```ts
// Recursively makes all properties in an object type optional, including nested objects
type DeepPartial<T> = T extends object 
  ? { [P in keyof T]?: DeepPartial<T[P]> }
  : T;
```

The key simplification here is removing the redundant `T[P] extends object ? DeepPartial<T[P]> : T[P]` check. Since `DeepPartial<T[P]>` already handles the case where `T[P]` is not an object (it would just return `T[P]` unchanged), we can apply `DeepPartial` to all property types and let the recursion handle the base cases naturally.

This maintains the exact same behavior while being more concise and easier to read.
